ir printed in the output\\n   324→3. **Run `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}`** — this skill analyzes artifacts and diagnoses the root cause\\n   325→4. **Implement the minimum fix** — don't over-engineer; fix only what the test demands\\n   326→5. **Re-run the failing test** — not the whole suite, just the one test\\n   327→\\n   328→## Key Patterns to Follow\\n   329→\\n   330→- **Use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]`** for parsing hook stdin JSON\\n   331→- **Use `paths.WorktreeRoot()`** not `os.Getwd()` for git-relative paths\\n   332→- **Preserve unknown config keys** when modifying agent config files (don't clobber user settings)\\n   333→- **Use `logging.Debug/Info/Warn/Error`** for internal logging, not `fmt.Print`\\n   334→- **Keep interface implementations minimal** — only implement what's needed\\n   335→- **Follow Go idioms** from `.golangci.yml` — check before writing code\\n   336→\\n   337→## Output\\n   338→\\n   339→Summarize what was implemented:\\n   340→- Package directory and files created\\n   341→- Interfaces implemented (core + optional)\\n   342→- Hook names registered\\n   343→- E2E tiers passing (list which E2E tests pass)\\n   344→- Unit test coverage (number of test functions, what they cover — written in Step 14)\\n   345→- Any gaps or TODOs remaining\\n   346→- Commands to run full validation\\n   347→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"9e0c1bc2-e95d-4755-a433-569203cc1e04\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:53:04.359Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md\",\"content\":\"# Implement Command\\n\\nBuild the agent Go package using strict E2E-first TDD. Unit tests are written ONLY after all E2E tests pass.\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\n- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md`\\n- The E2E test runner already added (from `write-tests` command)\\n- If no one-pager exists, read the agent's docs and ask the user about hook even